{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}} {{Use South African English|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox rugby biography | name = Lionel Cronjé | image = | fullname = <!--if different--> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|05|25|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Bloemfontein]], [[South Africa]] | height = {{height|m=1.84}} | weight = {{Geobox2 unit/weight|kg|92}} | nickname = | occupation = | school = [[Queen's College (South Africa)|Queen's College]] | university = [[University of the Free State]] | relatives = | position = [[Fly-half (rugby union)|Fly-half]] / [[Centre (rugby union)|Centre]] / [[Fullback (rugby union)|Fullback]] | currentclub = [[Toyota Verblitz]] | youthyears1 = 2005–2007 | youthclubs1 = {{Rut Border Bulldogs}} | youthyears2 = 2008–2009 | youthclubs2 = {{Rut Free State Cheetahs}} | years1 = 2009 | clubs1 = {{Rut Free State Cheetahs}} | apps1 = 0 | points1 = 0 | years2 = 2010–2011 | clubs2 = {{Rut Stormers}} | apps2 = 7 | points2 = 32 | years3 = 2010–2011 | clubs3 = {{Rut Western Province}} | apps3 = 21 | points3 = 135 | years4 = 2012 | clubs4 = {{Rut Blue Bulls}} | apps4 = 5 | points4 = 0 | years5 = 2013 | clubs5 = {{Rut Golden Lions XV}} | apps5 = 5 | points5 = 19 | years6 = 2013 | clubs6 = {{Rut Golden Lions}} | apps6 = 5 | points6 = 0 | years7 = 2014 | clubs7 = {{Rut Brumbies}} | apps7 = 10 | points7 = 32 | years8 = 2014–2015 | clubs8 = {{Rut Sharks (Currie Cup)|CC=y}} | apps8 = 16 | points8 = 81 | years9 = 2015 | clubs9 = {{Rut Sharks XV}} | apps9 = 2 | points9 = 8 | years10 = 2015 | clubs10 = {{Rut Sharks}} | apps10 = 7 | points10 = 22 | years11 = 2017 | clubs11 = {{Rut Southern Kings}} | apps11 = 14 | points11 = 136 | years12 = 2017–present | clubs12 = [[Toyota Verblitz]] | apps12 = 16 | points12 = 148 | amatyears1 = 2009 | amatteam1 = {{Rut UFS Shimlas}} | amatcaps1 = 3 | amatpoints1 = 10 | repyears1 = 2009 | repteam1 = [[South Africa national under-20 rugby union team|South Africa Under-20]] | repcaps1 = 4 | reppoints1 = 29 | repyears2 = 2017 | repteam2 = [[South Africa 'A' national rugby union team|South Africa 'A']] | repcaps2 = 2 | reppoints2 = 4 | clubupdate = 22 April 2018 | repupdate = 22 April 2018 }}
'''Lionel Cronjé''' (born 25 May 1989) is a South African [[rugby union]] footballer, currently playing for [[Japan]]ese [[Top League]] side [[Toyota Verblitz]]. He is a versatile back-line player who can operate as a [[Rugby union positions#10. Fly-half|fly-half]] or [[Rugby union positions#15. Fullback|full-back]].
==Career==
Cronjé previously played for the [[Stormers]] and [[Western Province Rugby Union|Western Province]] before making the move north ahead of the [[2012 Super Rugby season]].<ref>[http://www.supersport.com/rugby/currie-cup/news/110919/Blue_Bulls_sign_Cronj http://www.supersport.com/rugby/currie-cup/news/110919/Blue_Bulls_sign_Cronj]</ref> He could play only five matches for the Blue Bulls due to a chest injury suffered in February 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mg.co.za/article/2012-02-28-bulls-without-cronj-for-super-rugby-season/|title=Bulls without Cronjé for Super Rugby season|last=Reporter|first=Staff|work=The M&G Online|access-date=2018-01-09|language=en}}</ref>
He joined the {{Rut Lions}} for 2013<ref name="Bulls' Cronjé off to the Lions">{{cite web | url=http://www.sport24.co.za/Rugby/Bulls-Lionel-Cronje-off-to-the-Lions-20121120 | title=Bulls' Cronjé off to the Lions | publisher=Sport24 | date=20 November 2012 | accessdate=20 November 2012}}</ref> and the {{Rut Brumbies}} for 2014.<ref name="Lionel Cronje to join Brumbies">{{cite web | url=http://www.sport24.co.za/Rugby/Super15/Lionel-Cronje-to-join-Brumbies-20131021 | title=Lionel Cronje to join Brumbies | publisher=Sport24 | date=21 October 2013 | accessdate=21 October 2013}}</ref>
He returned to South Africa later in 2014, signing a two-year deal with [[Durban]]-based side the {{Rut Sharks (Currie Cup)}}.<ref name="Lionel Cronje may miss Gungahlin Eagles' John I Dent semi after signing with Coastal Sharks">{{cite web | url=http://www.smh.com.au/rugby-union/lionel-cronje-may-miss-gungahlin-eagles-john-i-dent-semi-after-signing-with-coastal-sharks-20140727-zxd6w.html | title=Lionel Cronje may miss Gungahlin Eagles' John I Dent semi after signing with Coastal Sharks | publisher=Fairfax | work=Sydney Morning Herald | date=27 July 2014 | accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref> He was released by the Sharks in November 2015.<ref name="Training squad announcement">{{cite press release|url=http://www.sharksrugby.co.za/index.php/component/articles/?view=article&id=2843020 |title=Training squad announcement |publisher=Sharks |date=19 November 2015 |accessdate=19 November 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119225214/http://www.sharksrugby.co.za/index.php/component/articles/?view=article&id=2843020 |archivedate=19 November 2015 |df= }}</ref>
He joined [[Japan]]ese [[Top League]] side [[Toyota Verblitz]] for the [[2017–18 Top League|2017–18 season]].<ref name="Bulls' Jenkins off to Japan">{{cite news|url=https://www.supersport.com/rugby/sa-rugby/news/170504/Jenkins_signs_in_Japan |title=Bulls' Jenkins off to Japan |work=SuperSport |date=4 May 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505114731/https://www.supersport.com/rugby/sa-rugby/news/170504/Jenkins_signs_in_Japan |accessdate=5 May 2017 |archivedate= 5 May 2017 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref>
