A '''theft prevention agent''' is a [[security officer]] who participates in a working [[surveillance]] in public buildings whose core business is the [[Sales|sale]] in order to prevent theft, attacks and malicious acts. Its activity is exercised within the institution. He has a mission to control the level of access the store and [[POS terminals]], as well as preventive monitoring mission flights it performs at the [[sales floor]].

In France, it may proceed with the [[arrest]] of alleged offenders in accordance with Article 73 of the [[Code of Criminal Procedure]],He immediately report its findings to the management of the institution and prepares a report on its operations.

